---
import ReportLayout from "../../../layouts/ReportLayout.astro";
import Section from "../../../components/Section.astro";
import DiagramFigure from "../../../components/diagrams/DiagramFigure.astro";
import BotOnboardingLayersFlow from "../../../components/diagrams/BotOnboardingLayersFlow.astro";
import { chapterHref, chapterNavItems } from "../../../lib/chapters";
import { chrome, localePath } from "../../../lib/i18n";

const locale = "en" as const;
const nav = chapterNavItems(locale);
const t = chrome(locale);
const selfHref = localePath(locale, "guides/bot-im");
const ch01 = chapterHref("01-log-is-the-runtime", locale);
---

<ReportLayout
  title="Bot / IM onboarding · Agent Atelier"
  description="Maka Desktop IM QR onboarding and runtime bridges: onboarding ≠ long-lived bridge; secrets stay in main; CAS rollback; BotMessageEvent boundary — companion report, not a seventh worldview chapter."
  nav={nav}
  activeHref={selfHref}
  locale={locale}
>
  <article class="report">
    <header class="masthead">
      <p class="masthead__eyebrow">Companion guide · Specimen: maka-agent · {t.doneLabel}</p>
      <h1>
        <span class="masthead__title-zh">Bot / IM 接入</span>
        <span class="masthead__title-en">Bot onboarding &amp; IM bridges</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="masthead__sub">
        Product surface: how QR and manual config land in Settings → BotRegistry → SessionManager.
        Orthogonal to §01–§06 Runtime worldview — enter via
        <a href={`${ch01}#trust`}>§01 · #trust</a>, then this page.
      </p>
      <div class="masthead__meta">
        <span>Home · /guides/bot-im</span>
        <span>Research · #58 · Task · #69</span>
        <span>
          <a href={localePath("zh", "guides/bot-im")}>中文</a>
        </span>
      </div>
    </header>

    <Section
      id="scene"
      label="Bot · Scene"
      title="Two paths, one runtime"
      lede="QR and manual config both land in the same channel settings + BotRegistry — no second bot runtime."
    >
      <p>
        Maka Desktop IM supports QR onboarding (DingTalk / Feishu·Lark / WeCom / WeChat) that obtains
        credentials and enables a channel, or provider-specific manual config as fallback. Runtime
        <code>BotRegistry</code> also has Discord / QQ bridges — <strong>manual config only</strong>;
        they are not in the QR onboarding provider list (<code>BOT_ONBOARDING_PROVIDERS</code> is the
        four QR providers). Onboarding is a <strong>main-process capability</strong>: it does not
        enter the MCP manager and does not write agent session JSONL. When docs disagree,
        <strong>code + contract tests win</strong>.
      </p>
      <blockquote class="pull">
        Onboarding is ephemeral QR/session; the bridge is long-lived. Secrets never cross preload.
      </blockquote>
    </Section>

    <Section
      id="four-layers"
      label="Bot · Layers"
      title="Four layers: contract → service → settings effects → runtime bots"
      lede="Renderer holds a redacted snapshot only; device codes, poll tokens, and secrets live in main."
    >
      <DiagramFigure
        caption="Fig. · UI → BotOnboardingService → SettingsStore.updateIf → BotRegistry bridge; footer pins BotMessageEvent → SessionManager."
        alt="Four layers: Renderer modal, OnboardingService, SettingsStore CAS, BotRegistry; footer message boundary into SessionManager."
      >
        <BotOnboardingLayersFlow />
      </DiagramFigure>
      <ol class="plain-list numbered">
        <li>
          <code>@maka/core/bot-onboarding</code> — provider / brand / state / renderer-safe snapshot
          contract; no I/O.
        </li>
        <li>
          Desktop main <code>BotOnboardingService</code> — session authority, HTTP polling, credential
          persistence, cancel rollback, runtime effects.
        </li>
        <li>
          <code>applySettingsRuntimeEffects</code> → <code>BotRegistry</code> channel reconcile.
        </li>
        <li>
          <code>@maka/runtime/bots</code> — long-lived connections, message mapping,
          <code>allowedUserIds</code>, send.
        </li>
      </ol>
    </Section>

    <Section
      id="state-machine"
      label="Bot · State"
      title="State machine: waiting → connected / cancelled"
      lede="Renderer holds an opaque sessionId only; a new same-provider session aborts the old one."
    >
      <pre class="code-block" aria-label="Onboarding state machine">[*] → waiting (QR ready)
waiting / scanned → connecting (confirmed)
connecting → connected (persisted + runtime applied)
waiting / scanned → expired | denied | cancelled | error
connecting → cancelled (+ guarded rollback)</pre>
      <p>
        Snapshot fields are fixed: <code>sessionId</code>, <code>provider</code>, optional
        <code>brand</code>, <code>state</code>, optional QR data URL / expiry /
        <code>nextPollAfterMs</code>, <code>canOpenInBrowser</code>, non-sensitive identity, redacted
        error. When credentials are saved but the bridge is not healthy, surface a
        <code>warning</code> — honest notice, not a fake connected state.
      </p>
    </Section>

    <Section
      id="rollback-cas"
      label="Bot · Rollback"
      title="Credential commit and cancel: updateIf CAS"
      lede="Roll back only fields owned by this onboarding; exclude volatile status from the CAS predicate."
    >
      <ol class="plain-list numbered">
        <li>Read previous channel snapshot.</li>
        <li>
          Map credentials → channel patch (<code>enabled: true</code>,
          <code>readiness: configured</code>).
        </li>
        <li>Atomic settings write.</li>
        <li><code>applySettingsRuntimeEffects</code> → BotRegistry reconcile.</li>
        <li>Re-check current-session fence and AbortSignal after every await boundary.</li>
      </ol>
      <p>
        On cancel, <code>SettingsStore.updateIf(predicate, patch)</code> applies previous values only
        while owned identity fields still equal this write. Volatile status fields stay out of the
        predicate so an unrelated status write cannot silently no-op rollback. Platforms have no
        unified revoke — cancel only stops local polling, blocks late credential writes, and runs
        guarded rollback after the commit window.
      </p>
    </Section>

    <Section
      id="message-boundary"
      label="Bot · Messages"
      title="Message boundary: BotMessageEvent → turn"
      lede="Onboarding’s in-memory session map ≠ the agent ledger; the ledger starts only on the incoming path."
    >
      <pre class="code-block" aria-label="Message boundary">platform payload
  → bridge map → BotMessageEvent
  → bot-incoming-main
  → SessionManager (turn / JSONL)</pre>
      <p>
        Allowlist is <code>allowedUserIds</code> — no remote pairing approval. Allowlist-only changes
        may update policy in place; credential / domain / enabled changes stop the old bridge and
        create a new one.
      </p>
    </Section>

    <Section
      id="failure"
      label="Bot · Failure"
      title="Failure stories"
      lede="Prefer stopping local work over pretending the platform revoked anything."
    >
      <ul class="plain-list">
        <li>Abort / session-fence change → stop polling; late credentials never land</li>
        <li>CAS predicate mismatch → rollback no-op (someone else changed owned fields)</li>
        <li>Non-allowlist user → never reaches SessionManager turn</li>
        <li>Bridge credential / domain / enabled change → stop old → create new (not in-place hot swap)</li>
        <li>Discord / QQ: product surface is manual-only — do not teach QR onboarding as wired</li>
        <li>No platform revoke promise — cancel only clears local state</li>
      </ul>
    </Section>

    <Section
      id="nongoals"
      label="Bot · Non-goals"
      title="Explicitly out of V1"
      lede="Destination does not require stuffing IM product UX into §01–§06."
    >
      <ul class="plain-list">
        <li>Platform-side revoke / delete of a created app</li>
        <li>Multi-account and parallel same-provider onboarding</li>
        <li>Keychain at-rest encryption (today: owner-only settings + masked IPC)</li>
        <li>Remote message pairing approval</li>
      </ul>
      <aside class="history-aside">
        <p class="history-aside__tag">Verification</p>
        <p>
          Mechanism intro:
          <a href={localePath("en", "history/pr/1197")}>maka:pr:1197</a>. Tests:
          <code>bot-onboarding-main.test.ts</code> · e2e <code>bot-onboarding.spec.ts</code> ·
          <code>packages/runtime/src/bots/__tests__/*</code> ·
          <code>bot-incoming-*.test.ts</code>. Outline:
          <code>docs/research/bot-im-onboarding-deep-outline.md</code>.
        </p>
      </aside>
    </Section>
  </article>
</ReportLayout>

<style>
  .pull {
    margin: 1.1rem 0 0;
    padding: 0.85rem 1rem;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
    background: var(--softer);
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    max-width: 38em;
  }
  .plain-list {
    margin: 0.75rem 0 1.1rem;
    padding-left: 1.2rem;
    max-width: 42em;
  }
  .plain-list.numbered {
    list-style: decimal;
  }
  .plain-list li {
    margin-bottom: 0.45rem;
  }
  .code-block {
    margin: 1rem 0 1.25rem;
    padding: 0.9rem 1.05rem;
    background: var(--soft);
    border: 1px solid var(--hair);
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    overflow-x: auto;
    max-width: 42em;
    white-space: pre;
  }
</style>
